Sec. 161.139. REFUSAL TO PERMIT INSPECTION OF SHIPMENT. (a) A
person commits an offense if the person:
(1) refuses to permit inspection of animals under Section
161.048 of this code; or
(2) fails to stop a truck, trailer, wagon, or automobile
suspected of carrying animals or animal products if requested or
signaled to do so by an agent of the commission.
(b) An offense under this section is a Class C misdemeanor
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 913 -

AGRICULTURE CODE

unless it is shown on the trial of the offense that the defendant has
been previously convicted under this section, in which event the
offense is a Class B misdemeanor.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1405, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 1989, 71st Leg., ch. 836, Sec. 24, eff. Sept. 1,
